[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"671004\">@Danilo Krummrich</span> I am working a bit on the <code>nvme</code> driver, rebasing it on upstream. I<br>\nran some trouble with the upstream PCI interrupt API, and I wanted to hear if<br>\nI'm holding it wrong, or if this is by design.</p>\n<p>How do I reallocate irq vectors? Looking at the code, it looks like<br>\n<code>IrqVectorRegistration::register</code> sticks the registration in <code>devres</code> and<br>\nforgets about it. I need to change the interrupt configuration as part of<br>\nsetting up the device. In C, this involves tearing down existing vectors with<br>\n<code>bindings::pci_free_irq_vectors</code> and then starting over. Is there a way to do<br>\nthis with the Rust API? If not, have you thought about this situation?</p>",
        "id": 577490949,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1772715198
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is also unclear to me how to iterate the <code>RangeInclusive&lt;IrqVector&lt;'_&gt;&gt;</code> returned by <code>pci::Device&lt;_&gt;::alloc_irq_vectors</code>. <code>IrqVector&lt;'_&gt;</code> does not implement <code>Step</code> so it cannot be turned into an iterator. I cannot get <code>IrqVector</code> instances for the middle of the range?</p>",
        "id": 577514327,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1772721066
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>RangeInclusive</code> is an odd choice here, I think we should just replace it with a new type <code>IrqVectors</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">diff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pci</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pci</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">af74ddff6114</span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"mi\">84420</span><span class=\"n\">d86e9b2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">100644</span>\n<span class=\"o\">---</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pci</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+++</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pci</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">51</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">51</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">@@</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">irq</span><span class=\"p\">::{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">IrqType</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">IrqTypes</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVector</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">//</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVector</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVectors</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">//</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sd\">/// An adapter for the registration of PCI drivers.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">diff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pci</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">irq</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pci</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">irq</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d9230e105541</span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"mi\">21</span><span class=\"n\">f47cfa5054</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">100644</span>\n<span class=\"o\">---</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pci</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">irq</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+++</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pci</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">irq</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">17</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">17</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">6</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">@@</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"kt\">str</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">CStr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">sync</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">aref</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">ARef</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">//</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">ops</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">RangeInclusive</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sd\">/// IRQ type flags for PCI interrupt allocation.</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy)]</span>\n<span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">112</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">6</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">111</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">85</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">try_into</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">IrqRequest</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"sd\">/// The set of IRQ vectors allocated for a PCI device.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"sd\">/// Returned by [`Device::alloc_irq_vectors`]. Provides indexed access and iteration over the</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"sd\">/// allocated [`IrqVector`]s.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"sd\">/// # Invariants</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"sd\">/// `count` is the number of IRQ vectors successfully allocated for `dev`.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Clone, Copy)]</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">IrqVectors</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Device</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Bound</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">count</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVectors</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Returns the number of allocated IRQ vectors.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[allow(clippy::len_without_is_empty)]</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">len</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">count</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Returns the nth IRQ vector, or `None` if out of bounds.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">nth</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">IrqVector</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">count</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">None</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: `index` is within bounds of the allocated vectors.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVector</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Returns an iterator over all allocated IRQ vectors.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">iter</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">IrqVectorIter</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVectorIter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">count</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">count</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">IntoIterator</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVectors</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Item</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVector</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">IntoIter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVectorIter</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">into_iter</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">IntoIter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">iter</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"sd\">/// An iterator over the [`IrqVector`]s of an [`IrqVectors`] allocation.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">IrqVectorIter</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Device</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Bound</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">count</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Iterator</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVectorIter</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Item</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVector</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">next</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Item</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">count</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">None</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: `self.index` is within bounds of the allocated vectors.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">vector</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVector</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">vector</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">size_hint</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">usize</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">usize</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">remaining</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">count</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">usize</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">remaining</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">remaining</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">ExactSizeIterator</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IrqVectorIter</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"nb\">_</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 577553587,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1772730075
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Regarding reallocation of IRQ vectors, this isn't easily possible with the managed version we currently have, i.e. we currently rely on devres cleanup ordering, which ensures that the IRQ vector is not freed as long as the <code>irq::Registration</code> is still around.</p>\n<p>It could be addressed though, we could e.g. create a dedicated pci::irq::Registration type which owns a <code>pci::IrqVectorRegistration</code>.</p>\n<p>I assume this is needed for some FLR use-case?</p>",
        "id": 577555709,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1772730623
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not familiar with the FLR term?</p>",
        "id": 577561858,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1772732292
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Function Level Reset</p>",
        "id": 577562092,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1772732364
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"671004\">Danilo Krummrich</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Re-configuring.20interrupt.20vectors/near/577555709\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Regarding reallocation of IRQ vectors, this isn't easily possible with the managed version we currently have, i.e. we currently rely on devres cleanup ordering, which ensures that the IRQ vector is not freed as long as the <code>irq::Registration</code> is still around.</p>\n<p>It could be addressed though, we could e.g. create a dedicated pci::irq::Registration type which owns a <code>pci::IrqVectorRegistration</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I see. What I did for now is return the registration to the caller, instead of giving it to devres. But it's no good because the allocation registration can drop before the irq registration.</p>\n<p>I don't think tying the irq to the allocation with a lifetime is going to work, ergonomically. Probably reference counting is the way to go.</p>",
        "id": 577562943,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1772732647
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"671004\">Danilo Krummrich</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Re-configuring.20interrupt.20vectors/near/577562092\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Function Level Reset</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>No, it is part of device initialization. The details are not too important. The sort story is that communication with NVMe devices happens via ring buffers (queues). Device raises an interrupt when it has placed something in a queue for the driver to process. </p>\n<p>To initialize the device, the driver first sets up a special admin queue. It uses this queue to discover capabilities of the device. Configuration of an interrupt is required for this queue to work. Once the driver has obtained the required information, it sets up more queues, ideally spreading them out between the available CPU cores. Each queue gets its own interrupt with affinity for the core or numa domain it is assigned to.</p>\n<p>The C driver first allocates a singe irq with <code>pci_alloc_irq_vectors</code> and registers this for the admin queue. When it is ready to set up the data queues, it unregisters the interrupt and frees the interrupt with <code>pci_free_irq_vectors</code> before setting up with affinity.</p>",
        "id": 577567308,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1772733903
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Could the admin queue be kept around and repurposed as data queue?</p>",
        "id": 577570288,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1772734987
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"413824\">Gary Guo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Re-configuring.20interrupt.20vectors/near/577570288\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Could the admin queue be kept around and repurposed as data queue?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It is kept around, but not as a data queue. It is special. It is  required to be around for the whole ride to do control plane operations.</p>",
        "id": 577570799,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1772735167
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The admin queue is not torn down, just the interrupt allocation and registration is torn down and then set up again.</p>",
        "id": 577571209,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1772735298
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"498029\">Andreas Hindborg</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Re-configuring.20interrupt.20vectors/near/577562943\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"671004\">Danilo Krummrich</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Re-configuring.20interrupt.20vectors/near/577555709\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Regarding reallocation of IRQ vectors, this isn't easily possible with the managed version we currently have, i.e. we currently rely on devres cleanup ordering, which ensures that the IRQ vector is not freed as long as the <code>irq::Registration</code> is still around.</p>\n<p>It could be addressed though, we could e.g. create a dedicated pci::irq::Registration type which owns a <code>pci::IrqVectorRegistration</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I see. What I did for now is return the registration to the caller, instead of giving it to devres. But it's no good because the allocation registration can drop before the irq registration.</p>\n<p>I don't think tying the irq to the allocation with a lifetime is going to work, ergonomically. Probably reference counting is the way to go.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think it could work with a pin-init feature that let's us pass references to previously pinned structures to subsequently pinned structures, but that's not very flexible. So, I'd go for a reference count for this.</p>",
        "id": 577596401,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1772744332
    }
]